  "texts": [
    "AI-powered sensory evaluations are often conducted using ad hoc model architectures, inconsistent performance metrics, and proprietary data, making it difficult to assess reproducibility or compare results across studies.",
    "The absence of agreed-upon benchmarks limits collaborative development and slows methodological progress.",
    "For instance, models trained for odor classification may use incompatible label schemes or preprocessing pipelines, resulting in incompatible results.",
    "The field would benefit from community-driven efforts to establish shared protocols, open datasets, and standardized evaluation metrics tailored to sensory science.",
    "As the research landscape evolves, emerging technologies are increasingly shaping AI applications in olfactory and gustatory studies."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}